---
description: Always-on Cursor pointer to AGENTS.md plus Cursor-specific behaviors.
alwaysApply: true
---

- Read and follow `AGENTS.md` at the project root before any task. It is the
  source of truth for project conventions, scope, and git boundaries.
- Use Plan mode for anything beyond a true one-liner. Do not start editing
  until the user has approved the plan.
- For files larger than ~500 lines, prefer SEARCH/REPLACE-style edits over
  full-file rewrites. Keep diffs surgical.
- If a task looks like it will exceed ~300 lines of new/changed code, stop and
  propose a split before writing more.
- Never merge a PR. Never force-push. Pushing to a feature branch and opening
  a PR is fine; merging is the human's job.
